Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: Preconceptions about place
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b03z999j
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 1 Feb 1976
Understanding the world means losing some preconceptions about other places. This archive edition of Letter from America was recorded by one of two listeners, who between them taped and labelled over 650 Letter From America programmes from 1973 to 1989. It was restored by the BBC in 2014.